  "texts": [
    "Each degree of freedom represents one of the primary ways in which a robot can move or orient parts of itself independently.",
    "For example, a simple robotic arm with a base that rotates (1 DOF), an elbow that bends (1 DOF), and a wrist that can rotate (1 DOF) has a total of 3 degrees of freedom.",
    "Forward KinematicsKinematics-the study of motion without considering the forces that cause itplays a crucial role in understanding and analyzing the behavior of robotic manipulators.",
    "Robot kinematics, particularly, involves the analytical examination of a robot manipulator's motion, utilizing Cartesian and Quaternion spaces for modeling.",
    "The transformation between two Cartesian systems involves rotation and translation, represented through various methods including Euler angles, Hamilton's quaternions, and homogenous transformations."
  ],
